titles.title: To suspend temporarily the duty on acetic acid, [[2-chloro-4-fluoro-5- [(tetrahydro-3-oxo-1H, 3H-[1,3,4] thiadiazolo [3,4-a] pyridazin-1-ylidene) amino] phenyl] thio]-, methyl ester.

action.text: Referred to the House Committee on Ways and Means.
Referred to the Subcommittee on Trade.

committee.name: House Committee on Ways and Means
House Committee on Ways and Means

bill.summary: 3/5/1998--Introduced. Amends the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States to suspend, through December 31, 2000, the duty on acetic acid, ((2- chloro-4-fluoro-5-((tetrahydro-3-oxo-1H, 3H-(1,3,4) thiadiazolo (3,4- a) pyridazin-1-ylidene) amino) phenyl)thio)-, methyl ester.
